    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-4">

            <!--Pokémon-->

            <img class="rounded-circle" src="https://yt3.googleusercontent.com/pK5_z_dptxyLuGllTGH4voHjz6WNTv0vgysrHQtmK6X45fl8g_h1ytu1H-ir1ExvY8uph0MbQA=s900-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj" alt="Pikachu" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Pokémon</h2>
            <p>Is the world's highest grossing media franchise, at an estimated $88 billion in revenue</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_highest-grossing_media_franchises" role="button">View more on Wikipedia</a></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">

            <!--Pac-Man-->

            <img class="rounded-circle" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Original_PacMan.svg/640px-Original_PacMan.svg.png" alt="Pac-man" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Pac-Man</h2>
            <p>Is litteraly designed as a Pizza missing a slice! In 1980, the developers had ordered a pizza and found the inspiration for the titular game character based on the food!</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://www.pacman.com/en/" role="button">Check out Pac-Man's Website</a></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
        <div class="col-lg-4">

            <!--Tetris-->

            <img class="rounded-circle" src="https://www.cnet.com/a/img/resize/a90802aafc4161528b929224c344a17c9c74c872/hub/2020/01/22/be798775-3467-49ec-9cf7-8d72b7118f56/screen-shot-2020-01-22-at-2-33-43-pm.png?auto=webp&fit=crop&height=1200&width=1200" alt="Tetris" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Tetris</h2>
            <p>Was the first ever video game to be played in space. The cosmonaut Aleksandr A. Serebrov played the game on a GameBoy aboard a a Soyuz TM-17 rocket in 1993.</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://www.nintendo.com/us/store/products/tetris-99-switch/" role="button">Try Tetris 99 on Nintendo Switch!</a></p>
        </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
    </div><!-- /.row -->
    <!-- Three more columns for fun facts -->
